      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="dawenkou"></a>
        Dawenkou Culture
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=23649' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dàsènkǒu Wénhuà', 'Dawenkou Culture')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">大汶口文化</a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        Other Neolithic cultures in China included the <span class='bookTitle'>Hongshan Culture</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25527' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '紅山文化 Hóngshān Wénhuà', 'Hongshan Culture')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">红山文化</a> in northeast China, 
        <span class='bookTitle'>Dawenkou Culture</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=23649' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dàsènkǒu Wénhuà', 'Dawenkou Culture')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">大汶口文化</a> of Shandong, and the
        <span class='bookTitle'>Xindian</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26466' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xīndiàn Wénhuà', 'Xindian Culture')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">辛店文化</a> and <span class='bookTitle'>Qijia Culture</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26467' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '齊家文化 Qíjiā Wénhuà', 'Qijia Culture')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">齐家文化</a> both of Gansu.
        The pictures below show painted pottery from the <span class='bookTitle'>Dawenkou Culture</span>.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=painted_pottery_pot400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/painted_pottery_pot400.jpg' alt='painted pottery' title='painted pottery'/></a> 
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25503' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǎitáoqì', 'painted pottery')" 
          onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>彩陶器</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=23649' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dàsènkǒu Wénhuà', 'Dawenkou Culture')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">大汶口文化</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=910' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '約 yuē', 'approximately')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">约</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>4400〜<a href='/word_detail.php?id=681' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qián', 'in front of / before')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">前</a>3600<a href='/word_detail.php?id=438' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nián', 'year')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">年</a>）<br/>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1237' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '山東 Shāndōng', 'Shandong')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">山东</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=882' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shěng', 'province')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">省</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25508' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '兗州 Yǎnzhōu', 'Yanzhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">兖州</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=630' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shì​', 'market / city')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">市</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25509' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Wángyīn', 'Wangyin')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">王因</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=16561' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '遺址 yízhǐ', 'ruins / historic relics / a site')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">遗址</a>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=2887' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shǒudū​', 'capital city')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">首都</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Painted Pottery Pot</div>
          Early Dawenkou Culture (c. 4,400&mdash;3,600 BCE)<br/>
          Excavated from Wangyin Site, Yanzhou, Shandong.
          Capital Museum, Beijing
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The <span class='bookTitle'>Dawenkou Culture</span> (4,100&mdash;2,600 BCE) was a group of Neolithic communities centered around Shandong but also
        appearing in Anhui, Henan, and Jiangsu.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=bowl_dawenkou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/bowl_dawenkou400.jpg' alt='painted pottery' title='painted pottery'/></a> 
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25480' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǎitáo', 'painted pottery')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">彩陶</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3947' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '缽 bō', 'an alms bowl / patra')" 
